{"build_type":"library","description":"Spawn-context proof worker: receives its context pointer as the first argument (rdi, placed there by the spawn child path per worker-runtime-FINAL A8) -- the context is a pointer to the per-instance shared region its launcher allocated. It writes a fixed sentinel into the first slot of that region and returns. The parent, holding the same region pointer, reads the sentinel back, proving the context pointer reached the worker via rdi. No global state -- the only channel is the shared region pointed to by the received context.","module_name":"record-spawn-context-into-shared-marker","package_name":"record-spawn-context-into-shared-marker","function_definitions":{"record-spawn-context-into-shared-marker":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"ctx","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"sentinel","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":51967},{"instruction_type":"array_write","base":"ctx","index":"zero","value":"sentinel","scale":8},{"instruction_type":"return_statement","return_payload":{"value":"zero"}}]}}}